Operatives of the Vigilante Group of Nigeria, VGN, have arrested eight suspected hoodlums who allegedly killed Sani Mazadu, a lecturer at the Federal University, Gashua in Yobe State. It was gathered that the deceased was killed last month by members of one of the dreaded cult groups code-named Sara-Suka. The VGN Area Commander, Sai Kachalla who disclosed this to newsmen said the suspects are in the region of 16 and 20 years old. -Advertisement- He said, “The Command had initiated steps to bring all the perpetrators of the murders to face the full wrath of the law”.